HEADWORD: Zampogna
<hw>Zam*po"gna</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.]</ety>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A sort of bagpipe formerly in use among Italian
peasants. It is now almost obsolete.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>zampugna</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

